##Introduction
On Day 2, I worked with real sequencing data and performed quality control analysis using FastQC. I also practiced Linux commands for file handling and software installation.

##Tools Used
FastQC (for quality control of FASTQ files)
Ubuntu (WSL environment)

##Commands Practiced
- 'cd' → Navigate between directories
- 'ls' → List files in a directory
- 'head' → View first few lines of a file
- 'sudo apt update' → Update package list
- 'sudo apt install fastqc' → Install FastQC

##Practical Work
Navigated to the FASTQ file directory
Viewed sequence data using head command
Installed FastQC tool
Ran FastQC on the FASTQ file
Generated quality report

##Output Observed
FASTQ file contains nucleotide sequences and quality scores
FastQC report includes:
Per base sequence quality
GC content
Sequence length distribution
Adapter content
Observed that some parameters passed while others showed warnings/fail (as seen in report summary)

##Conclusion
This session helped me understand how to handle sequencing data and perform quality control analysis using FastQC, which is an important step in NGS data analysis.
